            <p>Indiana is one of the fifty states which form the United States of America country. The state ranks fairly high in population and fairly low in area compared to other states of the country. Popularly known as the ‘Hoosier State’, the state is located in the Midwestern region of the country. </p>
            <p>The state shares borders with Michigan, Ohio, Kentucky and Illinois. The state is bordered by the Ohio River to its south and the Wabash River to its west. The state is located on the banks of multiple rivers including White, Blue, Wabash, Whitewater, St. Joseph and Maumee which form important riverine systems of the state. </p>
            <p>The state can be roughly divided into two main geographical formations which are the Central Lowlands and Interior Low Plateaus. The state mostly experiences a humid and interior continental climate due to its distance from the coastline while its southern part experiences a subtropical climate due to its latitudinal position. </p>

